🧠 CORE LOG MODEL (MANDATORY)

Each log must be transformed into:

{
  "id": number,              // sequential index
  "timestamp": string,       // ISO
  "message": string,
  "raw": string
}

---

🧠 STATE MODEL (FRONTEND)

You MUST maintain:

logs: Log[]                  // current visible logs
lastSeenTimestamp: string    // cursor
pendingLogs: Log[]           // new logs not yet shown
newLogsCount: number
isAutoRefresh: boolean

---

🟢 INITIAL LOAD LOGIC (STRICT)

1. Fetch:

oc logs <pod> --tail=<N>

2. Parse logs into structured objects

3. Sort by timestamp ASC

4. Assign IDs:

id = 1...N

5. Set:

logs = parsedLogs
lastSeenTimestamp = lastLog.timestamp
pendingLogs = []
newLogsCount = 0

---

🟡 REFRESH LOGIC (CRITICAL)

On refresh:

oc logs <pod> --since-time=<lastSeenTimestamp>

---

🔵 STEP-BY-STEP MERGE ALGORITHM (MANDATORY)

Step 1: Parse new logs

Step 2: Remove duplicates

Duplicate = same "timestamp + message"

newLogs = fetchedLogs.filter(
  log => !logs.some(existing => 
    existing.timestamp === log.timestamp &&
    existing.message === log.message
  )
)

---

Step 3: If NO new logs → EXIT

---

Step 4: Append to pendingLogs ONLY

pendingLogs = [...pendingLogs, ...newLogs]
newLogsCount += newLogs.length

🚨 DO NOT touch visible logs yet

---

🔴 CRITICAL UI RULE

«NEW LOGS MUST NOT BE RENDERED AUTOMATICALLY»

---

🟣 SHOW NEW LOGS ACTION

When user clicks:

[Show X new logs]

Then:

Step 1: Merge pending into logs

logs = [...logs, ...pendingLogs]

---

Step 2: Re-assign IDs

logs = logs.map((log, index) => ({
  ...log,
  id: index + 1
}))

---

Step 3: Trim to last N

logs = logs.slice(-N)

---

Step 4: Update cursor

lastSeenTimestamp = logs[logs.length - 1].timestamp

---

Step 5: Reset pending

pendingLogs = []
newLogsCount = 0

